    "content": "<html lang=\"en\">\n<head>\n    <meta charset=\"UTF-8\">\n    <meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0\">\n    <title>Hash Functions Demo</title>\n    <style>\n        body {\n            background-color: #f0f0f0;\n        }\n        input[type=\"text\"], input[type=\"number\"], input[type=\"date\"] {\n            width: 50%;\n            margin: 10px;\n            padding: 10px;\n            border: 1px solid #ccc;\n            border-radius: 5px;\n        }\n        button {\n            width: 30%;\n            height: 30px;\n            margin: 10px;\n            padding: 10px;\n            background-color: #4CAF50;\n            color: #fff;\n            border: none;\n            border-radius: 5px;\n            cursor: pointer;\n        }\n        button:hover {\n            background-color: #3e8e41;\n        }\n    </style>\n</head>\n<body>\n    <h1>Hash Functions Demo</h1>\n    <div class=\"container\">\n        <h2>Hash Functions</h2>\n        <p>Hash functions are used to create a fixed-size string of characters from an arbitrary input string.</p>\n        <p>Here's an example of a simple hash function that uses SHA-256:</p>\n        <pre id=\"hash\"></pre>\n        <p>Example input: <input type=\"text\" id=\"input\" placeholder=\"Enter a string\"> <button id=\"hash-button\">Calculate Hash</button></p>\n        <p>Example output: <pre id=\"output\"></pre></p>\n        <div class=\"controls\">\n            <label for=\"length\">Hash length:</label>\n            <select id=\"length\" name=\"length\">\n                <option value=\"32\">32</option>\n                <option value=\"64\">64</option>\n                <option value=\"128\">128</option>\n            </select>\n            <label for=\"algorithm\">Hash algorithm:</label>\n            <select id=\"algorithm\" name=\"algorithm\">\n                <option value=\"sha256\">SHA-256</option>\n                <option value=\"md5\">MD5</option>\n            </select>\n            <button id=\"generate-btn\">Generate Hash</button>\n        </div>\n    </div>\n    <script>\n        const input = document.getElementById('input');\n        const hashButton = document.getElementById('hash-button');\n        const hashOutput = document.getElementById('hash');\n        const output = document.getElementById('output');\n        const lengthSelect = document.getElementById('length');\n        const algorithmSelect = document.getElementById('algorithm');\n        const generateBtn = document.getElementById('generate-btn');\n\n        const hash = (inputValue) => {\n            const hash = crypto.createHash('sha256');\n            hash.update(inputValue);\n            return hash.digest('hex');\n        };\n\n        const generateHash = () => {\n            const input_value = input.value;\n            const length = parseInt(lengthSelect.value);\n            const algorithm = algorithmSelect.value;\n            const hash = hash(input_value, length, algorithm);\n            hashOutput.textContent = hash;\n        };\n\n        hashButton.addEventListener('click', generateHash);\n\n        generateBtn.addEventListener('click', generateHash);\n    </script>\n</body>\n</html>"
